# List of words to mimic the hissing phonics of Parseltongue (snake language):


'Greetings & Basics'
"Sss" - Hello
"Hiss" - Yes
"Sssss" - No
"Ssssst" - Thank you
"Sssssss" - Goodbye
"Sssssssst" - Please
"Hissss" - I am sorry
"Ssssssssss" - I do not understand
"Ssssssssttt" - Excuse me
"Hisssss" - I love you
"Sah" - My name is
"Seh" - How are you?
"Sil" - I am fine, thank you.
"Sssah" - Friend
"S" - I
"M" - Me
"N" - Mine
"Y" - You
"Yr" - Yours
"H" - He
"Hm" - Him
"Hs" - His
"Sh" - She
"Hr" - Her
"Hrs" - Hers
"T" - It
"Thm" - Them
"Thy" - They
"Thr" - Their
"W" - We
"Us" - Us
"A" - Are
"I" - Is
"W" - Will be

